Cordulegaster trinacriae is a species of dragonfly in the family Cordulegastridae. It is endemic to central-southern Italy, from Abruzzo south to Calabria, and then in Sicily, from where it was first described (hence the scientific name) (Corso, A. 2019, 2020). Its natural habitats are humid forests, rivers, and freshwater springs. It is threatened by habitat loss.